<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880713-0121 </DOCNO><HL> International Corporate Report: Midland Sets Up New Unit For Third World Activities </HL><SO> </SO><IN> SCR BNK </IN><TEXT>   MIDLAND BANK PLC is setting up a new division to combine its commercial and investment-banking operations in developing countries.    The new unit will be part of Midland Montagu, Midland's international and investment-banking arm. A spokesman said the unit will provide Midland with a &quot;clearer focus&quot; by bringing related activities under one roof.    The spokesman said the creation of the unit demonstrated &quot;a greater commitment to debt-equity swaps&quot; on the part of Midland as a way of reducing its exposure to Third World debt. The unit will create a team to oversee the conversion of debt into equity in industrial companies. </TEXT></DOC>